# python-gcs — project rules for the agent

## What this is
A MAVLink ground control station. PyQt6 desktop app with a tabbed layout (FLY / PLAN / SETUP).
SIM: PX4 SITL (Gazebo, gz_x500 = the Holybro X500/S500 quad model).
REAL TARGET: Holybro S500 + Pixhawk 6C, which ships with PX4 firmware.
Sim and target firmware now MATCH (both PX4). The codebase is being ported
FROM its old ArduCopter conventions TO PX4 — see "PX4 specifics" below.

## Stack
- Python 3, PyQt6, pymavlink (raw — not dronekit, not MAVSDK)
- 3D attitude viewer and map are QWebEngineView widgets running three.js /
  Leaflet from CDN inside Python HTML strings. Do NOT add external model files.

## File responsibilities
- main.py                  entry point: connect, request telemetry, launch GUI
- gcs/connection.py        connect(conn_str) + telemetry setup
- gcs/telemetry.py         pymavlink recv loop -> telemetry_data dict + msg handlers
- gcs/commands.py          flight commands, each a function taking `vehicle` first
- gcs/logs.py              log() writes to a shared buffer the console panel reads
- gcs/ui/gui.py            GCSWindow, StatPanel, 3-column + bottom-bar layout, refresh
- gcs/ui/map_view.py       Leaflet map
- gcs/ui/attitude_view.py  three.js quad, update_attitude(roll,pitch,yaw) in RADIANS
- gcs/ui/console_view.py   reads the log buffer
- gcs/ui/camera_view.py    "NO SIGNAL" placeholders (no camera hardware yet)
- gcs/ui/setup_view.py     parameter viewer/editor interface
- gcs/ui/tile_server.py    local offline HTTP tile server and downloader

## Conventions — follow these exactly
- vehicle is a pymavlink mavutil connection. Commands send via
  vehicle.mav.*_send / vehicle.mav.send(...). Log start+end with log().
- GUI button handlers run commands in a daemon thread; never block the Qt
  main thread.
- Adding telemetry = add key to telemetry_data, add the message type to the
  recv filter, add a handler, then display it in GCSWindow.refresh().
- refresh() runs on a 500ms QTimer.
- Angles are radians internally, shown in degrees in the UI.
- Style buttons with self._btn_style(color, bg), inputs with _input_style().
  Palette: bg #f5f7fa, panel #ffffff, border #cbd5e1, primary(blue) #0b57d0,
  success(green) #0f9d58, warning(amber) #e37400, danger(red) #d93025,
  muted #5f6368, dark_text #0f172a. Font: Courier New.

## How to run / verify
- Sim, easy path (Windows-friendly, Docker):
    docker run --rm -it jonasvautherin/px4-gazebo-headless:1.16.1
  Forwards MAVLink to the host on 14550 (QGC) and 14540 (our app).
- Sim, from source: in PX4-Autopilot, `make px4_sitl gz_x500`.
- GCS connects to PX4's offboard/API port over UDP: udpin:localhost:14540
  (14550 is reserved for QGroundControl). NOT tcp:127.0.0.1:5760 anymore.
- The agent CANNOT fly the sim or watch the 3D model. Flight behavior is
  verified by the human running SITL and clicking buttons. Never claim a
  movement/attitude feature works without human confirmation in the sim.

## PX4 specifics — this is PX4, NOT ArduPilot. Do not reuse ArduPilot patterns.
- MODES: names differ. PX4 modes via pymavlink mode_mapping() include MANUAL,
  STABILIZED, ALTCTL, POSCTL, OFFBOARD, AUTO.LOITER, AUTO.RTL, AUTO.LAND,
  AUTO.TAKEOFF, AUTO.MISSION. There is NO "GUIDED". Update the mode dropdown to
  PX4 names. PX4 custom_mode is bit-packed (main + sub mode), so verify mode
  setting actually works; may require MAV_CMD_DO_SET_MODE instead of
  set_mode_send.
- TELEMETRY: PX4 ignores REQUEST_DATA_STREAM (that was ArduPilot). Either rely
  on PX4's default onboard stream on 14540, or request per-message rates with
  MAV_CMD_SET_MESSAGE_INTERVAL. The same message types still arrive (ATTITUDE,
  GLOBAL_POSITION_INT, SYS_STATUS, GPS_RAW_INT, VFR_HUD, HEARTBEAT, STATUSTEXT).
- YAW: MAV_CMD_CONDITION_YAW does not exist on PX4. Delete condition_yaw. Yaw is
  commanded via the yaw / yaw_rate field of the OFFBOARD setpoint.
- MOVEMENT: requires OFFBOARD mode, which requires, in order:
    1) stream setpoints (SET_POSITION_TARGET_LOCAL_NED) at >2 Hz (use ~10-20 Hz)
       BEFORE switching to OFFBOARD,
    2) switch to OFFBOARD,
    3) keep streaming — if the stream stops for ~0.5 s PX4 drops out of OFFBOARD.
  Implement a persistent background "offboard streamer" thread that always
  publishes the current desired body velocity + yaw_rate. FORWARD / YAW buttons
  just change those target values. This REPLACES the old one-shot move_body and
  condition_yaw.
- TAKEOFF: arm, then AUTO.TAKEOFF mode (or MAV_CMD_NAV_TAKEOFF). PX4 preflight
  checks (EKF/GPS) may block arming until the sim has a position fix.
- ARMING: MAV_CMD_COMPONENT_ARM_DISARM (param1 = 1 arm / 0 disarm), unchanged.
- RTL / LAND buttons map to AUTO.RTL / AUTO.LAND modes.